ish, American pianist and educator\nBULLET::::- 1936 – Omar Suleiman, Egyptian general and politician, 16th Vice President of Egypt (d. 2012)\nBULLET::::- 1937 – Polly Holliday, American actress\nBULLET::::- 1937 – Richard Petty, American race car driver and sportscaster\nBULLET::::- 1938 – David Owen, English physician and politician, Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs\nBULLET::::- 1939 – Alexandros Panagoulis, Greek poet and politician (d. 1976)\nBULLET::::- 1939 – John H. Sununu, American engineer and politician, 14th White House Chief of Staff\nBULLET::::- 1939 – Paul Williams, American singer and choreographer (d. 1973)\nBULLET::::- 1940 – Kenneth Clarke, English politician, Lord High Chancellor of Great Britain\nBULLET::::- 1941 – William Guest, American singer-songwriter and producer (d. 2015)\nBULLET::::- 1941 – Wendell Mottley, Trinidadian sprinter, economist, and politician\nBULLET::::- 1942 – John Eekelaar, South African-English lawyer and scholar\nBULLET::::- 1942 – Vicente Fox, Mexican businessman and politician, 35th President of Mexico (2000-2006)\nBULLET::::- 1943 – Ivi Eenmaa, Estonian politician, 36th Mayor of Tallinn\nBULLET::::- 1943 – Larry Lake, American-Canadian trumpet player and composer (d. 2013)\nBULLET::::- 1946 – Richard Axel, American neuroscientist and biologist, Nobel Prize laureate\nBULLET::::- 1946 – Ron Silver, American actor, director, and political activist (d. 2009)\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Larry David, American actor, comedian, producer, and screenwriter\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Ann Taylor, Baroness Taylor of Bolton, English politician, Minister for International Security Strategy\nBULLET::::- 1948 – Mutula Kilonzo, Kenyan lawyer and politician (d. 2013)\nBULLET::::- 1949 – Greg Brown, American musician\nBULLET::::- 1949 – Robert Paquette, Canadian singer-songwriter and guitarist\nBULLET::::- 1950 – Lynne Brindley, English librarian and academic\nBULLET::::- 1950 – Jon Trickett, English politician\nBULLET::::- 1952 –