ce\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Jim Beattie, American baseball player, coach, and manager\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Morganna, American model, actress, and dancer\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Devendra Kumar Joshi, 21st Chief of Naval Staff of the Indian Navy\nBULLET::::- 1955 – Kevin Nichols, Australian cyclist\nBULLET::::- 1956 – Robert Sinclair MacKay, British academic and educator\nBULLET::::- 1957 – Rein Lang, Estonian politician and diplomat, 25th Estonian Minister of Foreign Affairs\nBULLET::::- 1958 – Vera Leth, Greenlandic Ombudsman\nBULLET::::- 1958 – Kirk Pengilly, Australian guitarist, saxophonist, and songwriter\nBULLET::::- 1958 – Carl Valentine, English-Canadian footballer, coach, and manager\nBULLET::::- 1959 – Victoria Abril, Spanish actress and singer\nBULLET::::- 1960 – Roland Ratzenberger, Austrian race car driver (d. 1994)\nBULLET::::- 1961 – Richard Garriott, English-American video game designer, created the Ultima series\nBULLET::::- 1962 – Pam Shriver, American tennis player and sportscaster\nBULLET::::- 1963 – Henri Leconte, French tennis player and sportscaster\nBULLET::::- 1963 – Laureano Márquez, Spanish-Venezuelan political scientist and journalist\nBULLET::::- 1963 – José Oquendo, Puerto Rican-American baseball player and coach\nBULLET::::- 1963 – Sonia Pierre, Hatian-Dominican human rights activist (d. 2011)\nBULLET::::- 1964 – Cle Kooiman, American soccer player and manager\nBULLET::::- 1964 – Elie Saab, Lebanese fashion designer\nBULLET::::- 1964 – Edi Rama, Albanian politician\nBULLET::::- 1964 – Mark Slaughter, American singer-songwriter and producer\nBULLET::::- 1964 – Mark Whiting, American actor, director, and screenwriter\nBULLET::::- 1965 – Harvey Grant, American basketball player and coach\nBULLET::::- 1965 – Horace Grant, American basketball player and coach\nBULLET::::- 1965 – Kiriakos Karataidis, Greek footballer and manager\nBULLET::::- 1965 – Gérard Watkins, English actor and playwright\nBULLET::::- 1966 – Minas Hantzidis, German-Greek footballer